I"õ<ol>
  <li>Start cooking the white rice if you have not done it yet.</li>
  <li>Add 1 1/2 tablespoons of olive oil to a pan at medium heat</li>
  <li>Add the hot dog to the pan and fry it for 2-4 minutes.</li>
  <li>Add the scrambled eggs to the pan with the hot dog and fry them for 2-4 minutes.</li>
  <li>Take the hot dogs and scrambled eggs and put them into a bowl (we will use them later).</li>
  <li>Add 1 tablespoon of olive oil to the same pan at low heat.</li>
  <li>Add the minced garlic and freshly grated ginger and sautee them for 1/2 minute (Control the heat so that it does not burn right away)</li>
  <li>Add diced onions to the pan and fry them a little bit for another 4-5 minutes (gradually increase heat to medium)</li>
  <li>Once your white rice is ready, put it in a separate large bowl.</li>
  <li>Add 1 cup of cooked white rice, some scrambled eggs, hot dogs and scallions to the pan where the onions, garlic and ginger are cooking.</li>
  <li>Add 1 tablespoon of soy sauce to the mix (to taste).</li>
  <li>Sautee everything at low-medium heat for 1 minute</li>
  <li>Repeat steps 10-12 for another 3 times or until everything from all the bowls is gone (rice, scrambled eggs, hot dogs and scallions).</li>
  <li>Serve on a bowl ;)</li>
</ol>
